What you need to know:

The championship has drawn national record holders Mark Otieno (100m) and Hellen Syombua (400m) as athletes put their best foot forward ahead of the World Relay Championships trialsUnlike during the first leg of the series on January 9 where athletes battled in 150m, 300m, 500m, 1,000m and 1,600m;  Saturday’s competition will feature 100m, 200m, 100m hurdles, 400m, 800m and relaysOtieno, who represented Kenya in the 4x200m at the 2019 World Relays in Yokohama, Japan, said he will compete in 100m and 200m, having posted the fastest time of 15.5 seconds in 150m in the first leg